## Architecture

```
src/utils/ai/grok/           # Grok subscription auth, client, models, billing
src/ai-proxy/
  index.ts                   # CLI entry
  lib/
    server.ts                # Bun.serve routes
    providers/grok-subscription.ts  # upstream forward + body prep
    rewrite-upstream-body.ts        # model rewrite, tools normalize, messagesâ†’input
    chat-to-responses-body.ts       # messages â†’ input conversion
    translators/
      detect-request.ts             # Cursor UA / body detection
      responses-to-chat.ts          # routes stream vs non-stream
      responses-stream-translator.ts # LiteLLM-inspired event â†’ chat delta
      responses-to-chat-sse.ts      # streaming SSE rewrite
      responses-to-chat-json.ts       # non-stream JSON rewrite
      identity-pipeline.ts          # passthrough when translation off
```

### Request flow (Cursor Agent, translation auto)

1. `POST /v1/chat/completions` with `User-Agent: Cursor` + `messages`
2. `handleChatCompletions` â†’ `responsesToChat`
3. Upstream: `POST /responses` with `input` (converted from messages)
4. Response: Grok Responses API SSE/JSON â†’ rewritten to Chat Completions format

### Model ID format

`{account}/{providerSlug}/{upstreamModel}` â†’ e.g. `martin/grok/grok-composer-2.5-fast`

---

## Cursor errors fixed

| Error | Cause | Fix |
|-------|-------|-----|
| `Access to private networks is forbidden` | Cursor cloud can't hit localhost | Public tunnel `mac.foltyn.dev` |
| `Model not found: martin/grok/...` | Proxy model id forwarded upstream | `rewrite-upstream-body.ts` |
| `missing field name` (tools) | Cursor nested `tools[].function.name` | `normalizeGrokTool()` |
| `missing field input` | Chat body routed to `/responses` without `input` | `chat-to-responses-body.ts` |
| Raw Responses JSON to Cursor (non-stream) | No response transform | `responses-to-chat-json.ts` |
| Empty stream / no reasoning | Grok uses `response.reasoning_text.delta` | `responses-stream-translator.ts` |

