## Verification commands

```bash
API_KEY="<proxyApiKey>"
MODEL="martin/grok/grok-composer-2.5-fast"

# Health
curl -s http://127.0.0.1:8317/health

# Non-stream (should return chat.completion, not raw response object)
curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8317/v1/chat/completions \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $API_KEY" -H "User-Agent: Cursor/1.0" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d "{\"model\":\"$MODEL\",\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Reply with exactly: hello\"}],\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":50}"

# Stream (should emit reasoning_content + content deltas)
curl -s -N -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8317/v1/chat/completions \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $API_KEY" -H "User-Agent: Cursor/1.0" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d "{\"model\":\"$MODEL\",\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Reply with exactly: hello\"}],\"stream\":true,\"max_tokens\":100}"

# Tests
cd /Users/Martin/Tresors/Projects/GenesisTools.worktrees/ai-proxy
bun test src/ai-proxy/
```

**Tip:** Low `max_tokens` can look like a streaming bug â€” Grok burns tokens on `reasoning_text` before `output_text`.

